name: appProperties
desc:
A collection of arbitrary key-value pairs which are private to the requesting app.
Entries with null values are cleared in update and copy requests. These properties can only be retrieved using an authenticated request. An authenticated request uses an access token obtained with a OAuth 2 client ID. You cannot use an API key to retrieve private properties.

name: capabilities
desc: Output only. Capabilities the current user has on this file. Each capability corresponds to a fine-grained action that a user may take. For more information, see [Understand file capabilities](https://developers.google.com/workspace/drive/api/guides/manage-sharing#capabilities).

name: contentHints
desc: Additional information about the content of the file. These fields are never populated in responses.

name: contentRestrictions
desc: Restrictions for accessing the content of the file. Only populated if such a restriction exists.

name: copyRequiresWriterPermission
desc: Whether the options to copy, print, or download this file should be disabled for readers and commenters.

name: createdTime
desc: The time at which the file was created (RFC 3339 date-time).

name: description
desc: A short description of the file.

name: downloadRestrictions
desc: Download restrictions applied on the file.

name: driveId
desc: Output only. ID of the shared drive the file resides in. Only populated for items in shared drives.

name: explicitlyTrashed
desc: Output only. Whether the file has been explicitly trashed, as opposed to recursively trashed from a parent folder.

name: exportLinks
desc: Output only. Links for exporting Docs Editors files to specific formats.

name: fileExtension
desc: Output only. The final component of `fullFileExtension`. This is only available for files with binary content in Google Drive.

name: folderColorRgb
desc: The color for a folder or a shortcut to a folder as an RGB hex string. The supported colors are published in the `folderColorPalette` field of the [`about`](/workspace/drive/api/reference/rest/v3/about) resource. If an unsupported color is specified, the closest color in the palette is used instead.

name: fullFileExtension
desc: Output only. The full file extension extracted from the `name` field. May contain multiple concatenated extensions, such as "tar.gz". This is only available for files with binary content in Google Drive. This is automatically updated when the `name` field changes, however it's not cleared if the new name doesn't contain a valid extension.

name: hasAugmentedPermissions
desc: Output only. Whether there are permissions directly on this file. This field is only populated for items in shared drives.

name: hasThumbnail
desc: Output only. Whether this file has a thumbnail. This doesn't indicate whether the requesting app has access to the thumbnail. To check access, look for the presence of the thumbnailLink field.

name: headRevisionId
desc: Output only. The ID of the file's head revision. This is currently only available for files with binary content in Google Drive.

name: iconLink
desc: Output only. A static, unauthenticated link to the file's icon.

name: id
desc: The ID of the file.

name: imageMediaMetadata
desc: Output only. Additional metadata about image media, if available.

name: inheritedPermissionsDisabled
desc: Whether this file has inherited permissions disabled. Inherited permissions are enabled by default.

name: isAppAuthorized
desc: Output only. Whether the file was created or opened by the requesting app.

name: kind
desc: Output only. Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string `"drive#file"`.

name: labelInfo
desc: Output only. An overview of the labels on the file.

name: lastModifyingUser
desc: Output only. The last user to modify the file. This field is only populated when the last modification was performed by a signed-in user.

name: linkShareMetadata
desc: Contains details about the link URLs that clients are using to refer to this item.

name: md5Checksum
desc: Output only. The MD5 checksum for the content of the file. This is only applicable to files with binary content in Google Drive.

name: mimeType
desc: The MIME type of the file. Google Drive attempts to automatically detect an appropriate value from uploaded content, if no value is provided. The value cannot be changed unless a new revision is uploaded. If a file is created with a Google Doc MIME type, the uploaded content is imported, if possible. The supported import formats are published in the [`about`](/workspace/drive/api/reference/rest/v3/about) resource.

name: modifiedByMe
desc: Output only. Whether the file has been modified by this user.

name: modifiedByMeTime
desc: The last time the file was modified by the user (RFC 3339 date-time).

name: modifiedTime
desc: he last time the file was modified by anyone (RFC 3339 date-time). Note that setting modifiedTime will also update modifiedByMeTime for the user.

name: name
desc: The name of the file. This isn't necessarily unique within a folder. Note that for immutable items such as the top-level folders of shared drives, the My Drive root folder, and the Application Data folder, the name is constant.

name: originalFilename
desc: The original filename of the uploaded content if available, or else the original value of the `name` field. This is only available for files with binary content in Google Drive.

name: ownedByMe
desc: Output only. Whether the user owns the file. Not populated for items in shared drives.

name: owners
desc: Output only. The owner of this file. Only certain legacy files may have more than one owner. This field isn't populated for items in shared drives.

name: parents
desc: The ID of the parent folder containing the file. A file can only have one parent folder; specifying multiple parents isn't supported. If not specified as part of a create request, the file is placed directly in the user's My Drive folder. If not specified as part of a copy request, the file inherits any discoverable parent of the source file. Update requests must use the `addParents` and `removeParents` parameters to modify the parents list.

name: permissionIds
desc: Output only. List of permission IDs for users with access to this file.

name: permissions
desc: Output only. The full list of permissions for the file. This is only available if the requesting user can share the file. Not populated for items in shared drives.

name: properties
desc:
A collection of arbitrary key-value pairs which are visible to all apps.
Entries with null values are cleared in update and copy requests.

name: quotaBytesUsed
desc: Output only. The number of storage quota bytes used by the file. This includes the head revision as well as previous revisions with `keepForever` enabled.

name: resourceKey
desc: Output only. A key needed to access the item via a shared link.

name: sha1Checksum
desc: Output only. The SHA1 checksum associated with this file, if available. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Google Drive; it's not populated for Docs Editors or shortcut files.

name: sha256Checksum
desc: Output only. The SHA256 checksum associated with this file, if available. This field is only populated for files with content stored in Google Drive; it's not populated for Docs Editors or shortcut files.

name: shared
desc: Output only. Whether the file has been shared. Not populated for items in shared drives.

name: sharedWithMeTime
desc: The time at which the file was shared with the user, if applicable (RFC 3339 date-time).

name: sharingUser
desc: Output only. The user who shared the file with the requesting user, if applicable.

name: shortcutDetails
desc: Shortcut file details. Only populated for shortcut files, which have the mimeType field set to `application/vnd.google-apps.shortcut`. Can only be set on `files.create` requests.

name: size
desc: Output only. Size in bytes of blobs and Google Workspace editor files. Won't be populated for files that have no size, like shortcuts and folders.

name: spaces
desc: Output only. The list of spaces which contain the file. The currently supported values are `drive`, `appDataFolder`, and `photos`.

name: starred
desc: Whether the user has starred the file.

name: teamDriveId
desc: Deprecated: Output only. Use `driveId` instead.

name: thumbnailLink
desc: Output only. A short-lived link to the file's thumbnail, if available. Typically lasts on the order of hours. Not intended for direct usage on web applications due to [Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS)](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CORS) policies. Consider using a proxy server. Only populated when the requesting app can access the file's content. If the file isn't shared publicly, the URL returned in `files.thumbnailLink` must be fetched using a credentialed request.

name: thumbnailVersion
desc: Output only. The thumbnail version for use in thumbnail cache invalidation.

name: trashed
desc: Whether the file has been trashed, either explicitly or from a trashed parent folder. Only the owner may trash a file, and other users cannot see files in the owner's trash.

name: trashedTime
desc: The time that the item was trashed (RFC 3339 date-time). Only populated for items in shared drives.

name: trashingUser
desc: Output only. If the file has been explicitly trashed, the user who trashed it. Only populated for items in shared drives.

name: version
desc: Output only. A monotonically increasing version number for the file. This reflects every change made to the file on the server, even those not visible to the user.

name: videoMediaMetadata
desc: Output only. Additional metadata about video media. This may not be available immediately upon upload.

name: viewedByMe
desc: Output only. Whether the file has been viewed by this user.

name: viewedByMeTime
desc: The last time the file was viewed by the user (RFC 3339 date-time).

name: viewersCanCopyContent
desc: Deprecated: Use `copyRequiresWriterPermission` instead.

name: webContentLink
desc: Output only. A link for downloading the content of the file in a browser. This is only available for files with binary content in Google Drive.

name: webViewLink
desc: Output only. A link for opening the file in a relevant Google editor or viewer in a browser.

name: writersCanShare
desc: Whether users with only `writer` permission can modify the file's permissions. Not populated for items in shared drives.
